-- Commodities Head for Longest Rally Since March 2005 on Gold, Cotton, Sugar
-- B y   S t e v e   S t r o t h
-- 2010-11-09T14:33:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-09/commodities-head-for-longest-rally-since-march-2005-on-gold-cotton-sugar.html
The Thomson Reuters/Jefferies CRB
Index of 19 commodities advanced for a ninth straight session,
heading for the longest rally since March 11, 2005.  The CRB rose 1 percent to 318.36 as of 9:32 a.m. in New
York, after touching 318.47, the highest level since Oct. 6,
2008. Gold and cotton touched records, silver reached a 30-year
high, and corn futures were the highest since August 2008. Sugar
posted the biggest gain on the index, rising as much as 3.9
percent to a 29-year high.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Stroth at 
 sstroth@bloomberg.net  